d infiniteci: The pure mathematics behind infinite confidence intervals for percentiles
d Applied statisticians frequently have reasons for calculating
d confidence intervals with infinite lower and upper limits,
d especially for percentiles and for percentile differences,
d ratios and slopes. This document gives a pure mathematical
d justification for this practice.
